The paper deals with domain adaptation, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on open set domain adaptation, which involves dealing with unknown target samples, and utilizes techniques related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) to exploit the semantic structure of the data. The paper also mentions the use of classifiers, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and benchmarks its performance on datasets, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
